This is a simple explanations with examples of Pythons code conventions.

| | |
|---|---|
|**ClassName**|Class name - used by **CamelCase** formatting|
|**\_\_special__**| Special method - marked with double underscore|
|**variable_name**|Variables name with more than 2 words|
|**variable**|Variables name with 1 word|

---
